# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is gitignored — never commit secrets.

# ── Server (Node) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# iSports Football API key — required for live data. Subscribe to the
# "Live Data" plan at https://www.isportsapi.com (the free trial caps at
# 200 calls/day; the 5s livescores loop exhausts it in under 20 minutes).
# Skip this if you only want offline fixture mode (see USE_FIXTURES below).
ISPORTS_API_KEY=your_key_here

# Offline fixture mode — set to "true" to skip iSports entirely and boot
# the server from a captured /schedule snapshot at
# server/fixtures/schedule-wc2026.json. The UI renders a full bracket
# with no live updates. Lets contributors develop without an API key.
# USE_FIXTURES=true

# Port the Node SSE server listens on. Defaults to 3001.
# PORT=3001

# ── Client (.ehpk build) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Absolute URL of the public-facing Node server. Baked into the bundle at
# build time (Vite reads VITE_* vars). Leave UNSET for dev — the vite
# proxy in vite.config.ts forwards /events to localhost:3001.
# Production example: VITE_SERVER_URL=https://wc.example.com
# VITE_SERVER_URL=
